Now with that information, what should you do if partner overcalls 1NT and your RHO passes.|
PG| ***** 12 ***** |


AT| The answer is very simple. You simply play "Front of Card" (FOC), referring to the section on responding to 1NT that appears on the ACBL Convention Card. Simply said, you use exactly the same methods you use when partner opens 1NT. They are you know:|
PG| ***** 13 ***** |


at|
^-
{    2@C is Stayman    }|
PG| ***** 14 ***** |


AT|

{    2@D is a transfer to hearts    }|
PG| ***** 15 ***** |


AT|

{    2@H is a transfer to spades    }|
PG| ***** 16 ***** |


AT|

{    2@S is transfer to minors if you play that convention    }|
PG| ***** 17 ***** |


AT|

{    Let us look at a few examples.    }
^-|
