NT|^B@2
Could you, in this bidding cycle, have a hand requiring a 2@D, transferring to 2@H?|
PG| ***** 24 ***** |


NT|^B@2
Given a 1@H opener, responder to 1NT could never have a hand where a 2@D transfer to 2@H is right, even if responder had 5+ hearts (highly unlikely). Having said that, it is too complicated to play 2@D as anything but a transfer (basically it is an impossible bid; only an expert partnership would come up with some other meaning).|
