This is a tough one. You have no rooms for misunderstanding. You may consider bidding 4@H as transfer to spade and partner can pass. So unless you have a firm partnership agreement take the safest route and bid 4@S.|mb|4s|
PG| ***** 55 ***** |


NT|^B@2
It is highly unlikely partner misunderstand the 4@S. On the other hand, it would bother you to say the least, if you bid 4@H as transfer and you see 3 passes followed your bid with a smile on you partner's face -:). However, some mature partnership safely use "Systems On-Stolen Bid" with no accident and 4@H to transfer to spades.|
